A declaration and ordinance of the Lords and Commons assembled in Parliament; touching the Great Seale of England. And that the said Seale is to be put into the hands and custody of such commissioners, as are herein named by both Houses of Parliament. Ordered by the Commons in Parliament, that this declaration touching the Great Seale, be forthwith printed and published: H: Elsynge, Cler. Parl. D. Com. England and Wales. Parliament.
8 p.
Printed for Edward Husbands, [London] : November 11. 1643.
Place of publication from Wing. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
